## **14. One instance overloaded, others idle**

![Image](https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/%24s_%214Uyj%21%2Cf_auto%2Cq_auto%3Agood%2Cfl_progressive%3Asteep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1a1213e2-86cb-4fa8-bf72-e37ffe0da44d_2250x2624.heic)

![Image](https://miro.medium.com/1%2AY4MhymjDWD-AsCrZgcwCyQ.png)

![Image](https://i.postimg.cc/Z52HRRLX/stickysession.jpg)

![Image](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/application-gateway/for-containers/media/session-affinity/session-affinity.png)

### 👉 Meaning:

Load not distributed evenly

### 🔍 Causes:

* Sticky sessions enabled
* Long-lived connections
* Uneven health

### ✅ Fix:

* Disable sticky sessions
* Use round-robin / least connection
* Check app-level session handling

---

## **15. Health checks failing**

### 🔍 Causes:

* Wrong endpoint (`/health` not working)
* Timeout too low
* App slow to respond
* SG blocking health check

### ✅ Fix:

* Test health endpoint manually
* Increase timeout
* Check logs
* Allow LB SG in EC2 SG

---

## **16. LB working but response slow**

### 🔍 Possible layers:

#### 1. Backend issue:

* High CPU / memory
* DB slow

#### 2. LB config:

* Idle timeout
* Connection reuse

#### 3. Network:

* Cross-AZ latency

### ✅ Fix:

* Check CloudWatch metrics
* Enable keep-alive
* Add caching / autoscaling

---

## **17. Sticky sessions issue**

### 👉 Problem:

User always routed to same instance

### 🔍 Causes:

* Session affinity enabled
* Cookie misconfiguration

### ✅ Fix:

* Disable sticky sessions
* Move session to Redis / DB

---

## **18. SSL not working on LB**

### 🔍 Causes:

* Certificate not attached
* Wrong listener (HTTP instead of HTTPS)
* Expired cert
* Wrong domain

### ✅ Fix:

* Attach cert via AWS Certificate Manager
* Configure HTTPS listener (443)
* Check domain mapping

---

## **19. Target group has no healthy instances**

### 👉 Same as 503 but deeper

### 🔍 Causes:

* Health check failing
* Wrong port/path
* App not running
* SG issue

### ✅ Fix:

* Check health check logs
* SSH into instance → test endpoint
* Validate port

---

## **20. Wrong routing to instances (GitHub repo case)**

### 👉 Meaning:

Traffic going to wrong service/version

### 🔍 Causes:

* Wrong path-based routing
* Wrong target group mapping
* Listener rule priority issue

### ✅ Fix:

* Check listener rules
* Verify path patterns (`/api/*`)
* Validate target group mapping

